WEBVTT

00:07.908 --> 00:10.076
(horns honking)

00:11.378 --> 00:12.445
Come on!

00:12.447 --> 00:13.613
Get out of the street!

00:13.615 --> 00:15.381
Let's go!

00:15.383 --> 00:17.550
Get out of the damn street,
you freakin' lunatic!

00:17.552 --> 00:20.453
Yo, somebody get a net
for this whackjob, huh?

00:20.455 --> 00:22.188
Hey, pipe down, okay?

00:22.190 --> 00:23.823
Come on, lady!
We're taking care of it.

00:23.825 --> 00:25.658
(horn honks)

00:25.660 --> 00:26.659
Looks like an EDP.

00:26.661 --> 00:27.793
Some kind of
mental disorder.

00:27.795 --> 00:29.061
I hate these
kind of calls.

00:29.063 --> 00:30.363
How do you want
to handle it?

00:30.365 --> 00:31.897
Let's try and
talk to her.

00:31.899 --> 00:34.066
Hey...
Excuse us...

00:34.068 --> 00:35.101
Hey, excuse me.

00:35.103 --> 00:36.135
Excuse us.

00:36.137 --> 00:37.737
Where is it?

00:37.739 --> 00:38.704
They said it was

00:38.706 --> 00:40.206
going to be here,

00:40.208 --> 00:41.207
it's supposed to be here.

00:41.209 --> 00:42.241
Did you lose
something?

00:42.243 --> 00:43.676
If I don't bring it back,

00:43.678 --> 00:45.678
I-I don't know what they'll do.

00:45.680 --> 00:46.946
Look, whatever it is
you're looking for,

00:46.948 --> 00:49.081
maybe if you tell us what it is,
we can help you out.

00:50.984 --> 00:52.551
I-I can't.

00:52.553 --> 00:54.620
They'll hurt me if I tell you.

00:55.555 --> 00:56.389
Who's gonna hurt you?

00:56.391 --> 00:58.324
(horn honking)

00:58.326 --> 00:59.925
While we're young!

00:59.927 --> 01:01.227
Touch that horn one more time

01:01.229 --> 01:03.129
and I'm gonna feed you
the steering wheel.

01:04.665 --> 01:05.831
What's your name?

01:05.833 --> 01:08.801
J... Jenny Strong.

01:08.803 --> 01:10.536
But I can't leave.

01:10.538 --> 01:12.738
They're watching me.

01:12.740 --> 01:14.907
Okay, well, look, whatever it is
you're looking for,

01:14.909 --> 01:18.077
it'll probably be easier to find
once traffic dies down, right?

01:18.079 --> 01:19.912
(horn blares)

01:19.914 --> 01:21.147
I-I guess so.

01:21.149 --> 01:22.314
So why don't you
come with us now,

01:22.316 --> 01:24.583
and then you can come back later

01:24.585 --> 01:26.352
and find whatever it is
you're looking for.

01:26.354 --> 01:27.353
What do you say?

01:27.355 --> 01:30.389
(horns honking)

01:33.760 --> 01:36.629
I guess so.

01:37.831 --> 01:39.031
Okay, great.

01:43.070 --> 01:44.570
(drivers cheering)

01:44.572 --> 01:47.239
CAB DRIVER: Yeah, let's get you two
some medals, huh?

01:47.241 --> 01:49.442
Way to go.

01:52.345 --> 01:53.713
We did have a good case, sir,

01:53.715 --> 01:56.649
but Jane Cooley is
a damn good defense attorney--

01:58.051 --> 01:59.251
I get it. No...

01:59.253 --> 02:02.688
Taking down Grazioso is
a priority for this office.

02:02.690 --> 02:04.323
We just...

02:04.325 --> 02:05.524
Hello?

02:07.327 --> 02:09.695
Guess we'll talk
about that later.

02:09.697 --> 02:10.996
You wanted to see me?

02:10.997 --> 02:12.164
Yeah, Jimmy, come on in.

02:12.166 --> 02:13.699
You heard Grazioso
was acquitted

02:13.701 --> 02:15.768
in his racketeering trial?

02:15.770 --> 02:17.470
It's easier to catch
a snake than kill it.

02:17.472 --> 02:19.305
Fortune cookie
wisdom aside,

02:19.307 --> 02:21.006
he runs a major
crime organization

02:21.008 --> 02:22.408
and we need to take him down.

02:22.410 --> 02:24.243
Crazy Lenny's a mob boss, Erin.

02:24.245 --> 02:25.511
He doesn't do
the dirty work anymore.

02:25.513 --> 02:27.379
He gives the orders.
Very, very tough to prove.

02:27.381 --> 02:29.548
Which is why I've been digging
through unsolved crimes

02:29.550 --> 02:31.317
where Grazioso was a suspect.

02:31.319 --> 02:34.220
(laughs) You're gonna need
a pretty big shovel for that.

02:34.222 --> 02:35.254
That's what I thought,

02:35.256 --> 02:38.357
till I saw your name
pop up in a file.

02:38.359 --> 02:40.025
Oh...

02:40.027 --> 02:42.561
Oh, Ronald Green murder.

02:42.563 --> 02:43.963
Hell's Kitchen.

02:43.965 --> 02:46.098
I was just a patrol cop
back then.

02:46.100 --> 02:47.767
ERIN: File says that you
and your partner

02:47.769 --> 02:49.368
were the first ones
on the scene.

02:49.370 --> 02:52.204
Grazioso was questioned,
but never charged.

02:52.206 --> 02:53.773
All true.

02:53.775 --> 02:55.841
Lenny was a soldier
in those days.

02:55.843 --> 02:57.276
Toughest guy on the street.

02:57.278 --> 02:59.378
Lenny warned Green
not to deal on his turf.

02:59.380 --> 03:02.181
Green didn't listen...
end of Green.

03:02.183 --> 03:04.884
But with no witnesses
and no weapon...

03:04.886 --> 03:06.552
Grazioso skated. As usual.

03:06.554 --> 03:09.121
Not to mention when a real
bad guy like Green gets killed,

03:09.123 --> 03:11.924
NYPD doesn't exactly bend over
backwards to make the case.

03:11.926 --> 03:14.894
I'd like to change that ending.

03:14.896 --> 03:16.295
I know it's a long shot,

03:16.297 --> 03:18.264
but I'm gonna reopen
the Green homicide.

03:18.266 --> 03:19.732
I need a lead
investigator

03:19.734 --> 03:22.201
that knows the territory.

03:22.203 --> 03:23.569
Any interest?

03:25.000 --> 03:31.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:32.012 --> 03:34.246
Sounds like it got
pretty crazy out there.

03:34.248 --> 03:36.148
Standard vehicle fire.
That's our turf.

03:36.150 --> 03:38.751
Unless the fire's the result
of a traffic accident

03:38.753 --> 03:41.420
with casualties--
which it was.

03:41.422 --> 03:44.023
Well, as long you're all okay.

03:44.025 --> 03:46.125
You guys are just pissed
there was no baby to save.

03:46.127 --> 03:48.160
OFFICER 2: Oh, please.
You hose jockeys

03:48.162 --> 03:49.662
are the biggest glory
hounds on the planet.

03:49.664 --> 03:51.030
LINDA:
Okay. Fellas.

03:51.032 --> 03:52.932
Remember,
we're all on the same team.

03:52.934 --> 03:54.300
Right?

03:54.302 --> 03:55.968
Yeah, well, nobody on our team
sleeps on duty.

03:55.970 --> 03:58.003
Yeah? Well, nobody on our team

03:58.005 --> 03:59.371
beats the hell out of
people for no reason.

03:59.373 --> 04:00.906
You're gonna want
to take that back.

04:00.908 --> 04:02.374
Okay, fellas, you know what?
Calm down, okay?

04:02.376 --> 04:03.843
Meter maid.
Hydrant boy!

04:03.845 --> 04:05.778
Ooh!
(grunting)

04:08.114 --> 04:10.149
Come on!
Security!

04:14.187 --> 04:16.154
I need security. Now.

04:16.156 --> 04:18.991
(grunting)

04:22.344 --> 04:26.344
<font color=#00FF00>♪ Blue Bloods 6x04 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>With Friends Like These</font>
